CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 10, 1945, pg. 24, reads: "Wedding Celebration Held - Celebrating the wedding of Miss Mary McNeil and Pvt. Oscar Vaughn Jr., friends and relatives gathered last Thursday for a delightful reception at the home of the bride's parents, Mrs. and Mrs. J. W. McNeil of Adelaide Street. The couple is shown with members of the wedding party and guests. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Group of women gathered around groom Pvt. Oscar Vaughn Jr. in Army uniform, and bride Mary McNeil Vaughn cutting wedding cake, in McNeil home, Adelaide Street, Upper Hill District
